"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fe5b59",
"children":[
"Ultrasonography is the initial imaging modality. Dilation of the cystic or biliary duct indicates an obstructing stone. Biliary colic is characterized by the episodic onset of acute, severe, epigastric or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"right upper quadrant",
"children":[
"RUQ"
]
},
" pain lasting 30 minutes to 6 hours and often accompanied by nausea and vomiting. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Fever, leukocytosis, and elevated liver enzymes indicate acute cholecystitis or obstruction of the common bile duct."
]
}
]
},
