"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d13e37",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 72-year-old woman is evaluated in the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intensive care unit",
"children":[
"ICU"
]
},
" for new-onset fever. She had been stable following treatment for urosepsis until now. Temperature is 38.2 °C (100.8 °F) and blood pressure is 90/62 mm Hg. RUQ tenderness is present. Ultrasound shows a distended gallbladder with wall thickening and pericholecystic fluid but no gallstones or dilated bile ducts."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"45d6c0",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose acalculous cholecystitis."
]
}
]
}
]
